U.S. Seeks to Improve Relations With Zimbabwe, Boost Trade, Embassy Says

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-09-13T15:50:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/u-s-seeks-to-improve-relations-with-zimbabwe-boost-trade-embassy-says.html
The U.S. is seeking to improve its
relations with  Zimbabwe  and will work with the country to
benefit its people, the U.S. embassy said.  The U.S. is focusing on boosting tourism and trade between
the countries and will host a half-day business seminar on
Zimbabwe during a U.S.-Africa summit in  Washington  in October,
the embassy in the southern African country said in an e-mailed
statement today, after Ambassador Charles Ray met with
Zimbabwean President  Robert Mugabe .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  